{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01StGfE9tdyB2W29BQkt8BaS","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.application;\n     2→\n     3→import java.time.LocalDate;\n     4→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n     5→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.internal.DefaultHandlingEventService;\n     6→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo;\n     7→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.RouteSpecification;\n     8→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\n     9→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEvent;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations;\n    11→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.SampleVoyages;\n    12→\n    13→public class HandlingEventServiceTest {\n    14→\n    15→  private DefaultHandlingEventService service;\n    16→  // private ApplicationEvents applicationEvents;\n    17→  // private CargoRepository cargoRepository;\n    18→  // private VoyageRepository voyageRepository;\n    19→  // private HandlingEventRepository handlingEventRepository;\n    20→  // private LocationRepository locationRepository;\n    21→  private Cargo cargo =\n    22→      new Cargo(\n    23→          new TrackingId(\"ABC\"),\n    24→          new RouteSpecification(SampleLocations.HAMBURG, SampleLocations.TOKYO, LocalDate.now()));\n    25→\n    26→  protected void setUp() throws Exception {\n    27→    // cargoRepository = createMock(CargoRepository.class);\n    28→    // voyageRepository = createMock(VoyageRepository.class);\n    29→    // handlingEventRepository = createMock(HandlingEventRepository.class);\n    30→    // locationRepository = createMock(LocationRepository.class);\n    31→    // applicationEvents = createMock(ApplicationEvents.class);\n    32→    // HandlingEventFactory handlingEventFactory = new HandlingEventFactory(\n    33→    // cargoRepository, voyageRepository, locationRepository);\n    34→    // service = new DefaultHandlingEventService(handlingEventRepository,\n    35→    // applicationEvents,\n    36→    // handlingEventFactory);\n    37→  }\n    38→\n    39→  protected void tearDown() throws Exception {\n    40→    // verify(cargoRepository, voyageRepository, handlingEventRepository,\n    41→    // applicationEvents);\n    42→  }\n    43→\n    44→  public void testRegisterEvent() throws Exception {\n    45→    // expect(cargoRepository.find(cargo.getTrackingId())).andReturn(cargo);\n    46→    // expect(voyageRepository.find(SampleVoyages.CM001.getVoyageNumber()))\n    47→    // .andReturn(SampleVoyages.CM001);\n    48→    // expect(locationRepository.find(SampleLocations.STOCKHOLM.getUnLocode()))\n    49→    // .andReturn(SampleLocations.STOCKHOLM);\n    50→    // handlingEventRepository.store(isA(HandlingEvent.class));\n    51→    // applicationEvents.cargoWasHandled(isA(HandlingEvent.class));\n    52→\n    53→    // replay(cargoRepository, voyageRepository, handlingEventRepository,\n    54→    // locationRepository, applicationEvents);\n    55→\n    56→    service.registerHandlingEvent(\n    57→        LocalDateTime.now(),\n    58→        cargo.getTrackingId(),\n    59→        SampleVoyages.CM001.getVoyageNumber(),\n    60→        SampleLocations.STOCKHOLM.getUnLocode(),\n    61→        HandlingEvent.Type.LOAD);\n    62→  }\n    63→}\n    64→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"83d9035c-c20b-4877-bffd-f348c2f149e2","uuid":"20c980de-f62a-4cdf-ac5c-9688ebfb2612"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Bgpqwmi9TarxNBLWSPdoFL","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.application;\n     2→\n     3→import io.quarkus.runtime.Startup;\n     4→import jakarta.annotation.PostConstruct;\n     5→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     6→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     7→\n     8→/** Loads sample data for demo. */\n     9→@ApplicationScoped\n    10→@Startup\n    11→public class BookingServiceTestDataGenerator {\n    12→\n    13→  @Inject\n    14→  private TestDataGenerator generator;\n    15→\n    16→  @PostConstruct\n    17→  public void loadSampleData() {\n    18→    // can't have @Transactional for calls inside the same class\n    19→    generator.loadData();\n    20→  }\n    21→\n    22→}\n    23→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"83d9035c-c20b-4877-bffd-f348c2f149e2","uuid":"5652321c-7648-44f1-bb51-dd446aab9e25"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_0196uzLUaxhZZ2QeCpV2W598","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.routing;\n     2→\n     3→import static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertEquals;\n     4→import static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertFalse;\n     5→import static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertNotNull;\n     6→\n     7→import java.time.LocalDate;\n     8→import java.util.List;\n     9→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Itinerary;\n    11→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.RouteSpecification;\n    12→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\n    13→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.Location;\n    14→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations;\n    15→\n    16→public class ExternalRoutingServiceTest {\n    17→\n    18→  private ExternalRoutingService externalRoutingService;\n    19→  // private VoyageRepository voyageRepository;\n    20→\n    21→  // protected void setUp() throws Exception {\n    22→  // externalRoutingService = new ExternalRoutingService();\n    23→  // LocationRepository locationRepository = new LocationRepositoryInMem();\n    24→  // externalRoutingService.setLocationRepository(locationRepository);\n    25→  //\n    26→  // voyageRepository = createMock(VoyageRepository.class);\n    27→  // externalRoutingService.setVoyageRepository(voyageRepository);\n    28→  //\n    29→  // GraphTraversalService graphTraversalService = new GraphTraversalServiceImpl(new\n    30→  // GraphDAO() {\n    31→  // public List<String> listLocations() {\n    32→  // return Arrays.asList(SampleLocations.TOKYO.getUnLocode().getIdString(),\n    33→  // SampleLocations.STOCKHOLM.getUnLocode().getIdString(),\n    34→  // SampleLocations.GOTHENBURG.getUnLocode().getIdString());\n    35→  // }\n    36→  //\n    37→  // public void storeCarrierMovementId(String cmId, String from, String to) {\n    38→  // }\n    39→  // });\n    40→  // externalRoutingService.setGraphTraversalService(graphTraversalService);\n    41→  // }\n    42→  // TODO [TDD] this test belongs in com.pathfinder\n    43→  public void testCalculatePossibleRoutes() {\n    44→    TrackingId trackingId = new TrackingId(\"ABC\");\n    45→    RouteSpecification routeSpecification =\n    46→        new RouteSpecification(SampleLocations.HONGKONG, SampleLocations.HELSINKI, LocalDate.now());\n    47→    Cargo cargo = new Cargo(trackingId, routeSpecification);\n    48→\n    49→    //\n    50→    // expect(voyageRepository.find(isA(VoyageNumber.class))).andStubReturn(SampleVoyages.CM002);\n    51→    //\n    52→    // replay(voyageRepository);\n    53→\n    54→    List<Itinerary> candidates =\n    55→        externalRoutingService.fetchRoutesForSpecification(routeSpecification);\n    56→    assertNotNull(candidates);\n    57→\n    58→    // Cargo origin and start of first leg should match\n    59→    // Cargo final destination and last leg stop should match\n    60→    // Assert that all legs are connected\n    61→    candidates\n    62→        .stream()\n    63→        .map(Itinerary::getLegs)\n    64→        .forEach(\n    65→            legs -> {\n    66→              assertNotNull(legs);\n    67→              assertFalse(legs.isEmpty());\n    68→              assertEquals(cargo.getOrigin(), legs.get(0).getLoadLocation());\n    69→              Location lastLegStop = legs.get(legs.size() - 1).getUnloadLocation();\n    70→              assertEquals(cargo.getRouteSpecification().getDestination(), lastLegStop);\n    71→              for (int i = 0; i < legs.size() - 1; i++) {\n    72→                assertEquals(legs.get(i).getUnloadLocation(), legs.get(i + 1).getLoadLocation());\n    73→              }\n    74→            });\n    75→\n    76→    // verify(voyageRepository);\n    77→  }\n    78→}\n    79→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"83d9035c-c20b-4877-bffd-f348c2f149e2","uuid":"dd6ca616-c9fb-40de-b800-36b5eb898f74"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01XAyfqbFeEvY9iisBeNaEUe","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.internal;\n     2→\n     3→import java.time.LocalDate;\n     4→import java.util.Collections;\n     5→import java.util.List;\n     6→import java.util.logging.Level;\n     7→import java.util.logging.Logger;\n     8→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     9→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n    10→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n    11→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.BookingService;\n    12→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo;\n    13→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.CargoRepository;\n    14→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Itinerary;\n    15→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.RouteSpecification;\n    16→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\n    17→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.Location;\n    18→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.LocationRepository;\n    19→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.UnLocode;\n    20→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.service.RoutingService;\n    21→\n    22→@ApplicationScoped\n    23→@Transactional\n    24→public class DefaultBookingService implements BookingService {\n    25→\n    26→  @Inject\n    27→  private CargoRepository cargoRepository;\n    28→  @Inject\n    29→  private LocationRepository locationRepository;\n    30→  @Inject\n    31→  private RoutingService routingService;\n    32→  @Inject\n    33→  private Logger logger;\n    34→\n    35→  @Override\n    36→  public TrackingId bookNewCargo(\n    37→      UnLocode originUnLocode, UnLocode destinationUnLocode, LocalDate arrivalDeadline) {\n    38→    TrackingId trackingId = cargoRepository.nextTrackingId();\n    39→    Location origin = locationRepository.find(originUnLocode);\n    40→    Location destination = locationRepository.find(destinationUnLocode);\n    41→    RouteSpecification routeSpecification =\n    42→        new RouteSpecification(origin, destination, arrivalDeadline);\n    43→\n    44→    Cargo cargo = new Cargo(trackingId, routeSpecification);\n    45→\n    46→    cargoRepository.store(cargo);\n    47→    logger.log(\n    48→        Level.INFO, \"Booked new cargo with tracking ID {0}\", cargo.getTrackingId().getIdString());\n    49→\n    50→    return cargo.getTrackingId();\n    51→  }\n    52→\n    53→  @Override\n    54→  public List<Itinerary> requestPossibleRoutesForCargo(TrackingId trackingId) {\n    55→    Cargo cargo = cargoRepository.find(trackingId);\n    56→\n    57→    if (cargo == null) {\n    58→      return Collections.emptyList();\n    59→    }\n    60→\n    61→    return routingService.fetchRoutesForSpecification(cargo.getRouteSpecification());\n    62→  }\n    63→\n    64→  @Override\n    65→  public void assignCargoToRoute(Itinerary itinerary, TrackingId trackingId) {\n    66→    Cargo cargo = cargoRepository.find(trackingId);\n    67→\n    68→    cargo.assignToRoute(itinerary);\n    69→    cargoRepository.store(cargo);\n    70→\n    71→    logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Assigned cargo {0} to new route\", trackingId);\n    72→  }\n    73→\n    74→  @Override\n    75→  public void changeDestination(TrackingId trackingId, UnLocode unLocode) {\n    76→    Cargo cargo = cargoRepository.find(trackingId);\n    77→    Location newDestination = locationRepository.find(unLocode);\n    78→\n    79→    RouteSpecification routeSpecification =\n    80→        new RouteSpecification(\n    81→            cargo.getOrigin(), newDestination, cargo.getRouteSpecification().getArrivalDeadline());\n    82→    cargo.specifyNewRoute(routeSpecification);\n    83→\n    84→    cargoRepository.store(cargo);\n    85→\n    86→    logger.log(\n    87→        Level.INFO,\n    88→        \"Changed destination for cargo {0} to {1}\",\n    89→        new Object[] {trackingId, routeSpecification.getDestination()});\n    90→  }\n    91→\n    92→  @Override\n    93→  public void changeDeadline(TrackingId trackingId, LocalDate newDeadline) {\n    94→    Cargo cargo = cargoRepository.find(trackingId);\n    95→\n    96→    RouteSpecification routeSpecification =\n    97→        new RouteSpecification(\n    98→            cargo.getOrigin(), cargo.getRouteSpecification().getDestination(), newDeadline);\n    99→    cargo.specifyNewRoute(routeSpecification);\n   100→\n   101→    cargoRepository.store(cargo);\n   102→\n   103→    logger.log(\n   104→        Level.INFO,\n   105→        \"Changed deadline for cargo {0} to {1}\",\n   106→        new Object[] {trackingId, newDeadline});\n   107→  }\n   108→}\n   109→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"83d9035c-c20b-4877-bffd-f348c2f149e2","uuid":"ae38bfd8-097e-43a8-b4a2-194797a9db8f"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_011oQFq2HtFdyBSvCDeJRg72","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.internal;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.logging.Level;\n     4→import java.util.logging.Logger;\n     5→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     6→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     7→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n     8→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.ApplicationEvents;\n     9→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.CargoInspectionService;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo;\n    11→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.CargoRepository;\n    12→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\n    13→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEventRepository;\n    14→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingHistory;\n    15→\n    16→@ApplicationScoped\n    17→@Transactional\n    18→public class DefaultCargoInspectionService implements CargoInspectionService {\n    19→\n    20→  @Inject\n    21→  private Logger logger;\n    22→  @Inject\n    23→  private ApplicationEvents applicationEvents;\n    24→  @Inject\n    25→  private CargoRepository cargoRepository;\n    26→  @Inject\n    27→  private HandlingEventRepository handlingEventRepository;\n    28→\n    29→  @Override\n    30→  public void inspectCargo(TrackingId trackingId) {\n    31→    Cargo cargo = cargoRepository.find(trackingId);\n    32→\n    33→    if (cargo == null) {\n    34→      logger.log(Level.WARNING, \"Can't inspect non-existing cargo {0}\", trackingId);\n    35→      return;\n    36→    }\n    37→\n    38→    HandlingHistory handlingHistory =\n    39→        handlingEventRepository.lookupHandlingHistoryOfCargo(trackingId);\n    40→\n    41→    cargo.deriveDeliveryProgress(handlingHistory);\n    42→\n    43→    if (cargo.getDelivery().isMisdirected()) {\n    44→      applicationEvents.cargoWasMisdirected(cargo);\n    45→    }\n    46→\n    47→    if (cargo.getDelivery().isUnloadedAtDestination()) {\n    48→      applicationEvents.cargoHasArrived(cargo);\n    49→    }\n    50→\n    51→    cargoRepository.store(cargo);\n    52→  }\n    53→}\n    54→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"83d9035c-c20b-4877-bffd-f348c2f149e2","uuid":"b54a550e-7bcf-4d08-adf7-90bb701311a0"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01UAWjVYsV4uMavWRXXu6XD9","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.internal;\n     2→\n     3→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n     4→import java.util.logging.Logger;\n     5→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     6→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.ApplicationEvents;\n     7→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.HandlingEventService;\n     8→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\n     9→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.CannotCreateHandlingEventException;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEvent;\n    11→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEventFactory;\n    12→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEventRepository;\n    13→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.UnLocode;\n    14→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.VoyageNumber;\n    15→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n    16→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n    17→\n    18→@ApplicationScoped\n    19→@Transactional(rollbackOn = CannotCreateHandlingEventException.class)\n    20→public class DefaultHandlingEventService implements HandlingEventService {\n    21→\n    22→  @Inject\n    23→  private ApplicationEvents applicationEvents;\n    24→  @Inject\n    25→  private HandlingEventRepository handlingEventRepository;\n    26→  @Inject\n    27→  private HandlingEventFactory handlingEventFactory;\n    28→  @Inject\n    29→  private Logger logger;\n    30→\n    31→  @Override\n    32→  public void registerHandlingEvent(\n    33→      LocalDateTime completionTime,\n    34→      TrackingId trackingId,\n    35→      VoyageNumber voyageNumber,\n    36→      UnLocode unLocode,\n    37→      HandlingEvent.Type type)\n    38→      throws CannotCreateHandlingEventException {\n    39→    LocalDateTime registrationTime = LocalDateTime.now();\n    40→\n    41→    /*\n    42→     * Using a factory to create a HandlingEvent (aggregate). This is where it is determined wether\n    43→     * the incoming data, the attempt, actually is capable of representing a real handling event.\n    44→     */\n    45→    HandlingEvent event =\n    46→        handlingEventFactory.createHandlingEvent(\n    47→            registrationTime, completionTime, trackingId, voyageNumber, unLocode, type);\n    48→\n    49→    /*\n    50→     * Store the new handling event, which updates the persistent state of the handling event\n    51→     * aggregate (but not the cargo aggregate - that happens asynchronously!)\n    52→     */\n    53→    handlingEventRepository.store(event);\n    54→\n    55→    /* Publish an event stating that a cargo has been handled. */\n    56→    applicationEvents.cargoWasHandled(event);\n    57→\n    58→    logger.info(\"Registered handling event\");\n    59→  }\n    60→}\n    61→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"83d9035c-c20b-4877-bffd-f348c2f149e2","uuid":"a1983886-7d33-47f2-b3fe-c311ca3b311e"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_013diZmELczPEAmLxjgF3ZDm","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the codebase. Let me identify all Quarkus-specific code patterns and plan the migration. Here's what I've found:\n\n**Quarkus-specific dependencies/code to migrate:**\n1. `io.quarkus.hibernate.orm.panache.PanacheRepositoryBase` - in all 4 repository classes\n2. `io.quarkus.panache.common.Parameters` - in all 4 repository classes\n3. `io.quarkus.runtime.StartupEvent` / `io.quarkus.runtime.ShutdownEvent` - in all 5 JMS consumers\n4. `io.quarkus.scheduler.Scheduled` - in UploadDirectoryScanner\n5. `io.quarkus.runtime.Startup` - in SampleDataGenerator and BookingServiceTestDataGenerator\n6. `io.quarkus.arc.profile.UnlessBuildProfile` - in SampleDataGenerator\n7. `io.quarkus.test.junit.QuarkusTest` - in BookingServiceTest\n8. `org.eclipse.microprofile.config.inject.ConfigProperty` - in JmsApplicationEvents, all consumers, ExternalRoutingService\n\n**Target: Jakarta EE (WildFly/Open Liberty traditional app server)**\n\nLet me now plan and execute the full migration:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6877,"cache_read_input_tokens":72316,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":6877,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":858},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"83d9035c-c20b-4877-bffd-f348c2f149e2","uuid":"67e3fd2e-4672-4368-8bac-ea1153bc21b4"}
