{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_019D57EXC3VUzyzDHpYGwBRR","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__jakarta/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/handling/file/UploadDirectoryScanner.java has been updated. Here's the result of running `cat -n` on a snippet of the edited file:\n     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.file;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.batch.operations.JobOperator;\n     4→import jakarta.batch.runtime.BatchRuntime;\n     5→import jakarta.ejb.Schedule;\n     6→import jakarta.ejb.Singleton;\n     7→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n     8→\n     9→/**\n    10→ * Periodically scans a certain directory for files and attempts to parse handling event\n    11→ * registrations from the contents by calling a batch job.\n    12→ */\n    13→@Singleton\n    14→@Transactional\n    15→public class UploadDirectoryScanner {\n    16→\n    17→  @Schedule(minute = \"*/2\", hour = \"*\", persistent = false)\n    18→  public void processFiles() {\n    19→    JobOperator jobOperator = BatchRuntime.getJobOperator();\n    20→    jobOperator.start(\"EventFilesProcessorJob\", null);\n    21→  }\n    22→}\n    23→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012q56QFf7xDBkCgsyeCsAu9","session_id":"83d9035c-c20b-4877-bffd-f348c2f149e2","uuid":"7d392af9-bf96-44ee-8365-7580c17a8049"}
