{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01TFh39d9WsdoL2nLLwuxwmA","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.persistence.jpa;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     5→import jakarta.persistence.EntityManager;\n     6→import jakarta.persistence.PersistenceContext;\n     7→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.Voyage;\n     8→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.VoyageNumber;\n     9→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.VoyageRepository;\n    10→\n    11→@ApplicationScoped\n    12→public class JpaVoyageRepository implements VoyageRepository, Serializable {\n    13→\n    14→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    15→\n    16→  @PersistenceContext\n    17→  private EntityManager entityManager;\n    18→\n    19→  @Override\n    20→  public Voyage find(VoyageNumber voyageNumber) {\n    21→    return entityManager.createNamedQuery(\"Voyage.findByVoyageNumber\", Voyage.class)\n    22→        .setParameter(\"voyageNumber\", voyageNumber)\n    23→        .getSingleResult();\n    24→  }\n    25→}\n    26→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"83d9035c-c20b-4877-bffd-f348c2f149e2","uuid":"e41b2c39-ae6e-4b88-b801-8b9dfbf7b667"}
