{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_011pmfdSwHFR8R9mKQYnGddN","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n     2→<project xmlns=\"http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0\" xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\" xsi:schemaLocation=\"http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0 https://maven.apache.org/xsd/maven-4.0.0.xsd\">\n     3→    <modelVersion>4.0.0</modelVersion>\n     4→    <groupId>org.eclipse.ee4j</groupId>\n     5→    <artifactId>cargo-tracker</artifactId>\n     6→    <version>1.0.0-SNAPSHOT</version>\n     7→    <packaging>war</packaging>\n     8→\n     9→    <properties>\n    10→        <maven.compiler.release>21</maven.compiler.release>\n    11→        <project.build.sourceEncoding>UTF-8</project.build.sourceEncoding>\n    12→        <project.reporting.outputEncoding>UTF-8</project.reporting.outputEncoding>\n    13→    </properties>\n    14→\n    15→    <dependencies>\n    16→        <!-- Jakarta EE 10 API -->\n    17→        <dependency>\n    18→            <groupId>jakarta.platform</groupId>\n    19→            <artifactId>jakarta.jakartaee-api</artifactId>\n    20→            <version>10.0.0</version>\n    21→            <scope>provided</scope>\n    22→        </dependency>\n    23→\n    24→        <!-- Apache Commons Lang (used in domain model) -->\n    25→        <dependency>\n    26→            <groupId>org.apache.commons</groupId>\n    27→            <artifactId>commons-lang3</artifactId>\n    28→            <version>3.14.0</version>\n    29→        </dependency>\n    30→\n    31→        <!-- Jackson for JSON support -->\n    32→        <dependency>\n    33→            <groupId>com.fasterxml.jackson.core</groupId>\n    34→            <artifactId>jackson-databind</artifactId>\n    35→            <version>2.17.0</version>\n    36→        </dependency>\n    37→        <dependency>\n    38→            <groupId>com.fasterxml.jackson.datatype</groupId>\n    39→            <artifactId>jackson-datatype-jsr310</artifactId>\n    40→            <version>2.17.0</version>\n    41→        </dependency>\n    42→        <dependency>\n    43→            <groupId>com.fasterxml.jackson.jakarta.rs</groupId>\n    44→            <artifactId>jackson-jakarta-rs-json-provider</artifactId>\n    45→            <version>2.17.0</version>\n    46→        </dependency>\n    47→\n    48→        <!-- PrimeFaces for JSF -->\n    49→        <dependency>\n    50→            <groupId>org.primefaces</groupId>\n    51→            <artifactId>primefaces</artifactId>\n    52→            <version>14.0.0</version>\n    53→            <classifier>jakarta</classifier>\n    54→        </dependency>\n    55→\n    56→        <!-- H2 Database (bundled for embedded use) -->\n    57→        <dependency>\n    58→            <groupId>com.h2database</groupId>\n    59→            <artifactId>h2</artifactId>\n    60→            <version>2.2.224</version>\n    61→        </dependency>\n    62→\n    63→        <!-- Test dependencies -->\n    64→        <dependency>\n    65→            <groupId>org.junit.jupiter</groupId>\n    66→            <artifactId>junit-jupiter</artifactId>\n    67→            <version>5.10.2</version>\n    68→            <scope>test</scope>\n    69→        </dependency>\n    70→    </dependencies>\n    71→\n    72→    <build>\n    73→        <finalName>cargo-tracker</finalName>\n    74→        <plugins>\n    75→            <plugin>\n    76→                <groupId>org.apache.maven.plugins</groupId>\n    77→                <artifactId>maven-compiler-plugin</artifactId>\n    78→                <version>3.14.0</version>\n    79→                <configuration>\n    80→                    <release>21</release>\n    81→                    <parameters>true</parameters>\n    82→                </configuration>\n    83→            </plugin>\n    84→            <plugin>\n    85→                <groupId>org.apache.maven.plugins</groupId>\n    86→                <artifactId>maven-war-plugin</artifactId>\n    87→                <version>3.4.0</version>\n    88→                <configuration>\n    89→                    <failOnMissingWebXml>false</failOnMissingWebXml>\n    90→                </configuration>\n    91→            </plugin>\n    92→            <plugin>\n    93→                <artifactId>maven-surefire-plugin</artifactId>\n    94→                <version>3.5.3</version>\n    95→            </plugin>\n    96→        </plugins>\n    97→    </build>\n    98→</project>\n    99→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"83d9035c-c20b-4877-bffd-f348c2f149e2","uuid":"f98fe362-dc33-4a95-a672-8cca68fd3410"}
