{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01SGQgVJNKobWq3pX2njrkrZ","type":"tool_result","content":"   130→\n   131→  @PostConstruct\n   132→  public void init() {\n   133→    List<Cargo> cargos = cargoRepository.listAll();\n   134→\n   135→    trackingIds = new ArrayList<>(cargos.size());\n   136→\n   137→    // List only routed cargo that is not claimed yet.\n   138→    cargos\n   139→        .stream()\n   140→        .filter(\n   141→            cargo -> !cargo.getItinerary().getLegs().isEmpty()\n   142→                && !(cargo\n   143→                    .getDelivery()\n   144→                    .getTransportStatus()\n   145→                    .sameValueAs(TransportStatus.CLAIMED)))\n   146→        .map(cargo -> cargo.getTrackingId().getIdString())\n   147→        .forEachOrdered(trackingId -> trackingIds.add(new SelectItem(trackingId, trackingId)));\n   148→\n   149→    List<Location> locations = locationRepository.findAll();\n   150→\n   151→    this.locations = new ArrayList<>(locations.size());\n   152→\n   153→    locations.forEach(\n   154→        location -> {\n   155→          String locationCode = location.getUnLocode().getIdString();\n   156→          this.locations.add(\n   157→              new SelectItem(locationCode, location.getName() + \" (\" + locationCode + \")\"));\n   158→        });\n   159→\n   160→    List<Voyage> voyages = voyageRepository.findAll();\n   161→\n   162→    this.voyages = new ArrayList<>(voyages.size());\n   163→\n   164→    voyages.forEach(\n   165→        voyage -> this.voyages.add(\n   166→            new SelectItem(\n   167→                voyage.getVoyageNumber().getIdString(),\n   168→                voyage.getVoyageNumber().getIdString())));\n   169→  }\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"83d9035c-c20b-4877-bffd-f348c2f149e2","uuid":"0f7a3a18-d2c1-4e86-9251-32e0149d75ce"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01BjoMK6botwWGxoQizDgYpg","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"`voyageRepository.findAll()` and `locationRepository.findAll()` look correct. `cargoRepository.listAll()` also correct since JpaCargoRepository has it. Now let me also check if there's a `listAll()` method on JpaLocationRepository (since the EventLogger injects `JpaLocationRepository` type and DefaultBookingServiceFacade also uses it):\n\nWait, looking at the DefaultBookingServiceFacade code again, it was importing `JpaLocationRepository` directly. But we changed `locationRepository.listAll()` to `locationRepository.findAll()`. The `JpaLocationRepository` class has `findAll()` method from the interface. This should work.\n\nNow let me attempt the Docker build. Let me update the todo and proceed:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":802,"cache_read_input_tokens":127882,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":802,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":714},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"83d9035c-c20b-4877-bffd-f348c2f149e2","uuid":"820e54f3-6c9b-4ba8-8697-9fdd93b51d2a"}
