{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Du5hsiCUfnESLu3WFRAqDU","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.web;\n     2→\n     3→import static java.util.stream.Collectors.toList;\n     4→\n     5→import java.util.List;\n     6→import jakarta.annotation.PostConstruct;\n     7→import jakarta.enterprise.context.RequestScoped;\n     8→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     9→import jakarta.inject.Named;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.BookingServiceFacade;\n    11→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.CargoRoute;\n    12→\n    13→/**\n    14→ * Handles listing cargo. Operates against a dedicated service facade, and could easily be rewritten\n    15→ * as a thick client. Completely separated from the domain layer, unlike the tracking user\n    16→ * interface.\n    17→ *\n    18→ * <p>\n    19→ * In order to successfully keep the domain model shielded from user interface considerations, this\n    20→ * approach is generally preferred to the one taken in the tracking controller. However, there is\n    21→ * never any one perfect solution for all situations, so we've chosen to demonstrate two polarized\n    22→ * ways to build user interfaces.\n    23→ */\n    24→@Named\n    25→@RequestScoped\n    26→public class ListCargo {\n    27→\n    28→  @Inject\n    29→  private BookingServiceFacade bookingServiceFacade;\n    30→\n    31→  private List<CargoRoute> notRoutedCargos;\n    32→  private List<CargoRoute> routedUnclaimedCargos;\n    33→  private List<CargoRoute> claimedCargos;\n    34→\n    35→  @PostConstruct\n    36→  public void init() {\n    37→    List<CargoRoute> cargos = bookingServiceFacade.listAllCargos();\n    38→    notRoutedCargos = cargos.stream().filter(route -> !route.isRouted()).collect(toList());\n    39→    routedUnclaimedCargos =\n    40→        cargos.stream().filter(route -> route.isRouted() && !route.isClaimed()).collect(toList());\n    41→    claimedCargos = cargos.stream().filter(CargoRoute::isClaimed).collect(toList());\n    42→  }\n    43→\n    44→  public List<CargoRoute> getNotRoutedCargos() {\n    45→    return notRoutedCargos;\n    46→  }\n    47→\n    48→  public List<CargoRoute> getRoutedUnclaimedCargos() {\n    49→    return routedUnclaimedCargos;\n    50→  }\n    51→\n    52→  public List<CargoRoute> getClaimedCargos() {\n    53→    return claimedCargos;\n    54→  }\n    55→}\n    56→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01VePpHzYZS6tXZbMyx7rDQ1","session_id":"83d9035c-c20b-4877-bffd-f348c2f149e2","uuid":"857dfe3d-7799-465c-b18d-0db4ebce9afe"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01REQahj31NZoaKw1qE92GqU","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Let me summarize the findings:\n\n1. XHTML Files:\nI found multiple .xhtml files, and they are all located in the `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__jakarta/run_2/output/src/main/resources/META-INF/resources/` directory. \n\nRegarding `event-logger.xhtml`: While there isn't a file with exactly that name, there is an `index.xhtml` in the `event-logger` subdirectory:\n- `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__jakarta/run_2/output/src/main/resources/META-INF/resources/event-logger/index.xhtml`\n\n2. Directory Structure:\nThe `resources/META-INF/resources/` directory has several subdirectories:\n- `WEB-INF/templates/common/`: Contains template XHTML files (public.xhtml, admin.xhtml)\n- `admin/`: Contains admin-related XHTML files\n  - Subdirectories: `dialogs/`, `tables/`, `tracking/`\n- `booking/`: Booking-related XHTML files\n- `event-logger/`: Contains event logger related files\n- `public/`: Public-facing XHTML files\n- `resources/`: Static resources\n  - Subdirectories: `css/`, `images/`, `js/`, `leaflet/`\n\n3. Webapp Directory:\nThe `src/main/webapp/` directory only contains a `WEB-INF` subdirectory, which is typical in Java web applications.\n\nKey Observations:\n- All XHTML files are located in `resources/META-INF/resources/`\n- The project uses a Quarkus/Jakarta structure\n- Web resources are well-organized into logical subdirectories\n\nWould you like me to provide more details about any of these files or directories?"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"83d9035c-c20b-4877-bffd-f348c2f149e2","uuid":"169196b0-b88a-419f-a5e7-1b0739c6a895"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01VePpHzYZS6tXZbMyx7rDQ1","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I have found and read both files as you requested. Here's a brief overview:\n\n1. CargoRouteDtoAssembler.java:\n   - Located at: `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__jakarta/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/booking/facade/internal/assembler/CargoRouteDtoAssembler.java`\n   - This is a DTO (Data Transfer Object) assembler class that converts a Cargo domain object to a CargoRoute DTO\n   - It uses a LocationDtoAssembler to convert locations\n   - The `toDto()` method transforms cargo information into a CargoRoute object with details like tracking ID, origin, destination, routing status, etc.\n\n2. ListCargo.java:\n   - Located at: `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__jakarta/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/booking/web/ListCargo.java`\n   - This is a request-scoped bean for listing cargo\n   - It uses BookingServiceFacade to retrieve all cargos\n   - The `init()` method categorizes cargos into three lists:\n     1. Not routed cargos\n     2. Routed but unclaimed cargos\n     3. Claimed cargos\n   - Provides getter methods for each cargo list\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any part of these files?"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"83d9035c-c20b-4877-bffd-f348c2f149e2","uuid":"91209aba-ab16-450f-ab1c-35024faee66a"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01M7GDJwHZwY1Tzf2Lf4Bjrw","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\nNow I understand both issues:\n\n1. **Event Logger 404**: The smoke test is requesting `/event-logger.xhtml` but the actual file is at `/event-logger/index.xhtml`. This is a smoke test URL issue, not an app bug.\n\n2. **Admin Dashboard 500**: NPE in `CargoRouteDtoAssembler.toDto()` - likely a null itinerary leg field during stream mapping.\n\nLet me look at the exact code causing the errors and fix both."}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1796,"cache_read_input_tokens":56077,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1796,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":337},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"83d9035c-c20b-4877-bffd-f348c2f149e2","uuid":"6bb82a55-2831-4d11-a9aa-eb634da2c29e"}
