{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01M7GDJwHZwY1Tzf2Lf4Bjrw","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01GHS34JwXv8Bu8hoSamvXmB","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__jakarta/run_2/output/smoke.py"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1796,"cache_read_input_tokens":56077,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1796,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":337},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"83d9035c-c20b-4877-bffd-f348c2f149e2","uuid":"5bea386f-a7d8-41e8-916a-778e5c602279"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01RrBCMLF7QinMBbGdLTGrN8","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.internal.assembler;\n     2→\n     3→import static java.util.stream.Collectors.toList;\n     4→\n     5→import java.util.List;\n     6→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     7→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     8→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo;\n     9→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.RoutingStatus;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TransportStatus;\n    11→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.CargoRoute;\n    12→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.Leg;\n    13→\n    14→@ApplicationScoped\n    15→public class CargoRouteDtoAssembler {\n    16→\n    17→  @Inject\n    18→  private LocationDtoAssembler locationDtoAssembler;\n    19→\n    20→  public CargoRoute toDto(Cargo cargo) {\n    21→    List<Leg> legs =\n    22→        cargo\n    23→            .getItinerary()\n    24→            .getLegs()\n    25→            .stream()\n    26→            .map(\n    27→                leg -> new Leg(\n    28→                    leg.getVoyage().getVoyageNumber().getIdString(),\n    29→                    locationDtoAssembler.toDto(leg.getLoadLocation()),\n    30→                    locationDtoAssembler.toDto(leg.getUnloadLocation()),\n    31→                    leg.getLoadTime(),\n    32→                    leg.getUnloadTime()))\n    33→            .collect(toList());\n    34→\n    35→    return new CargoRoute(\n    36→        cargo.getTrackingId().getIdString(),\n    37→        locationDtoAssembler.toDto(cargo.getOrigin()),\n    38→        locationDtoAssembler.toDto(cargo.getRouteSpecification().getDestination()),\n    39→        cargo.getRouteSpecification().getArrivalDeadline(),\n    40→        cargo.getDelivery().getRoutingStatus().sameValueAs(RoutingStatus.MISROUTED),\n    41→        cargo.getDelivery().getTransportStatus().sameValueAs(TransportStatus.CLAIMED),\n    42→        locationDtoAssembler.toDto(cargo.getDelivery().getLastKnownLocation()),\n    43→        cargo.getDelivery().getTransportStatus().name(),\n    44→        legs);\n    45→  }\n    46→}\n    47→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"83d9035c-c20b-4877-bffd-f348c2f149e2","uuid":"1313f367-742f-4432-9b6e-867cdb45611a"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01GHS34JwXv8Bu8hoSamvXmB","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→#!/usr/bin/env python3\n     2→\"\"\"Smoke tests for the CargoTracker Jakarta EE application.\"\"\"\n     3→\n     4→import json\n     5→import sys\n     6→import time\n     7→import urllib.request\n     8→import urllib.error\n     9→\n    10→BASE_URL = None\n    11→\n    12→def set_base_url(port):\n    13→    global BASE_URL\n    14→    BASE_URL = f\"http://localhost:{port}/cargo-tracker\"\n    15→\n    16→def test_rest_graph_traversal():\n    17→    \"\"\"Test the graph traversal REST endpoint.\"\"\"\n    18→    url = f\"{BASE_URL}/rest/graph-traversal/shortest-path?origin=CNHKG&destination=SESTO\"\n    19→    try:\n    20→        req = urllib.request.Request(url, headers={\"Accept\": \"application/json\"})\n    21→        with urllib.request.urlopen(req, timeout=30) as resp:\n    22→            assert resp.status == 200, f\"Expected 200, got {resp.status}\"\n    23→            data = json.loads(resp.read().decode())\n    24→            assert \"transitPaths\" in data, \"Response missing 'transitPaths' field\"\n    25→            assert len(data[\"transitPaths\"]) > 0, \"No transit paths returned\"\n    26→            for path in data[\"transitPaths\"]:\n    27→                assert \"transitEdges\" in path, \"Transit path missing 'transitEdges'\"\n    28→                assert len(path[\"transitEdges\"]) > 0, \"Transit path has no edges\"\n    29→            print(\"PASS: test_rest_graph_traversal\")\n    30→            return True\n    31→    except Exception as e:\n    32→        print(f\"FAIL: test_rest_graph_traversal - {e}\")\n    33→        return False\n    34→\n    35→def test_rest_handling_report():\n    36→    \"\"\"Test the handling report REST endpoint with a POST.\"\"\"\n    37→    url = f\"{BASE_URL}/rest/handling/reports\"\n    38→    payload = json.dumps({\n    39→        \"completionTime\": \"3/15/2026 12:00 PM\",\n    40→        \"trackingId\": \"ABC123\",\n    41→        \"eventType\": \"UNLOAD\",\n    42→        \"unLocode\": \"USDAL\",\n    43→        \"voyageNumber\": \"0200T\"\n    44→    }).encode()\n    45→    try:\n    46→        req = urllib.request.Request(\n    47→            url,\n    48→            data=payload,\n    49→            headers={\n    50→                \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\",\n    51→                \"Accept\": \"application/json\"\n    52→            },\n    53→            method=\"POST\"\n    54→        )\n    55→        with urllib.request.urlopen(req, timeout=30) as resp:\n    56→            # 200 or 204 are both acceptable\n    57→            assert resp.status in [200, 204], f\"Expected 200/204, got {resp.status}\"\n    58→            print(\"PASS: test_rest_handling_report\")\n    59→            return True\n    60→    except urllib.error.HTTPError as e:\n    61→        # A 400 is also acceptable if validation catches something;\n    62→        # we primarily want to confirm the endpoint exists and responds\n    63→        if e.code == 400:\n    64→            print(\"PASS: test_rest_handling_report (400 - validation working)\")\n    65→            return True\n    66→        print(f\"FAIL: test_rest_handling_report - HTTP {e.code}: {e.read().decode()[:200]}\")\n    67→        return False\n    68→    except Exception as e:\n    69→        print(f\"FAIL: test_rest_handling_report - {e}\")\n    70→        return False\n    71→\n    72→def test_app_root_accessible():\n    73→    \"\"\"Test that the application root context is accessible.\"\"\"\n    74→    url = f\"{BASE_URL}/\"\n    75→    try:\n    76→        req = urllib.request.Request(url)\n    77→        with urllib.request.urlopen(req, timeout=30) as resp:\n    78→            assert resp.status == 200, f\"Expected 200, got {resp.status}\"\n    79→            print(\"PASS: test_app_root_accessible\")\n    80→            return True\n    81→    except urllib.error.HTTPError as e:\n    82→        # 3xx redirects or JSF pages might return various codes\n    83→        if e.code in [301, 302, 303, 404]:\n    84→            print(f\"PASS: test_app_root_accessible (got {e.code}, server responding)\")\n    85→            return True\n    86→        print(f\"FAIL: test_app_root_accessible - HTTP {e.code}\")\n    87→        return False\n    88→    except Exception as e:\n    89→        print(f\"FAIL: test_app_root_accessible - {e}\")\n    90→        return False\n    91→\n    92→def test_rest_api_base():\n    93→    \"\"\"Test that the REST API base path is accessible.\"\"\"\n    94→    url = f\"{BASE_URL}/rest/graph-traversal/shortest-path?origin=CNHKG&destination=FIHEL\"\n    95→    try:\n    96→        req = urllib.request.Request(url, headers={\"Accept\": \"application/json\"})\n    97→        with urllib.request.urlopen(req, timeout=30) as resp:\n    98→            assert resp.status == 200, f\"Expected 200, got {resp.status}\"\n    99→            data = json.loads(resp.read().decode())\n   100→            assert \"transitPaths\" in data, \"Response missing transitPaths\"\n   101→            print(\"PASS: test_rest_api_base\")\n   102→            return True\n   103→    except Exception as e:\n   104→        print(f\"FAIL: test_rest_api_base - {e}\")\n   105→        return False\n   106→\n   107→def test_graph_traversal_validation():\n   108→    \"\"\"Test that invalid parameters are rejected.\"\"\"\n   109→    url = f\"{BASE_URL}/rest/graph-traversal/shortest-path?origin=XX&destination=YY\"\n   110→    try:\n   111→        req = urllib.request.Request(url, headers={\"Accept\": \"application/json\"})\n   112→        with urllib.request.urlopen(req, timeout=30) as resp:\n   113→            # If it returns 200 anyway, that's ok too\n   114→            print(\"PASS: test_graph_traversal_validation (endpoint responsive)\")\n   115→            return True\n   116→    except urllib.error.HTTPError as e:\n   117→        if e.code in [400, 500]:\n   118→            print(\"PASS: test_graph_traversal_validation (validation working)\")\n   119→            return True\n   120→        print(f\"FAIL: test_graph_traversal_validation - HTTP {e.code}\")\n   121→        return False\n   122→    except Exception as e:\n   123→        print(f\"FAIL: test_graph_traversal_validation - {e}\")\n   124→        return False\n   125→\n   126→def wait_for_server(max_wait=120):\n   127→    \"\"\"Wait for the server to be ready.\"\"\"\n   128→    url = f\"{BASE_URL}/rest/graph-traversal/shortest-path?origin=CNHKG&destination=SESTO\"\n   129→    print(f\"Waiting for server at {BASE_URL} ...\")\n   130→    start = time.time()\n   131→    while time.time() - start < max_wait:\n   132→        try:\n   133→            req = urllib.request.Request(url, headers={\"Accept\": \"application/json\"})\n   134→            with urllib.request.urlopen(req, timeout=5) as resp:\n   135→                if resp.status == 200:\n   136→                    print(f\"Server ready after {int(time.time() - start)}s\")\n   137→                    return True\n   138→        except Exception:\n   139→            pass\n   140→        time.sleep(3)\n   141→    print(f\"Server did not become ready within {max_wait}s\")\n   142→    return False\n   143→\n   144→def main():\n   145→    if len(sys.argv) < 2:\n   146→        print(\"Usage: python smoke.py <port>\")\n   147→        sys.exit(1)\n   148→\n   149→    port = sys.argv[1]\n   150→    set_base_url(port)\n   151→\n   152→    if not wait_for_server():\n   153→        print(\"FATAL: Server not available, aborting tests\")\n   154→        sys.exit(1)\n   155→\n   156→    tests = [\n   157→        test_app_root_accessible,\n   158→        test_rest_graph_traversal,\n   159→        test_rest_api_base,\n   160→        test_graph_traversal_validation,\n   161→        test_rest_handling_report,\n   162→    ]\n   163→\n   164→    results = []\n   165→    for test in tests:\n   166→        results.append(test())\n   167→\n   168→    passed = sum(1 for r in results if r)\n   169→    failed = sum(1 for r in results if not r)\n   170→    print(f\"\\n{'='*50}\")\n   171→    print(f\"Results: {passed} passed, {failed} failed, {len(results)} total\")\n   172→    print(f\"{'='*50}\")\n   173→\n   174→    sys.exit(0 if failed == 0 else 1)\n   175→\n   176→if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n   177→    main()\n   178→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"83d9035c-c20b-4877-bffd-f348c2f149e2","uuid":"5fd36932-a2e4-4d95-bc5b-6555becd18ee"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_0169JGyzbFCoceef3BLp7hEJ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I see - the smoke test in the container is actually a different version from what's on disk (the container has tests for admin/dashboard and event-logger pages, while smoke.py on disk has the simpler version). The container image was built from a previous state. But let me look at the actual error more carefully. The dashboard 500 is from `CargoRouteDtoAssembler.toDto()` at line 33. The issue is likely that some cargo has an empty itinerary (no legs), and calling `getLegs().stream()` on it causes a problem, OR one of the legs has a null voyage.\n\nLet me check the `Itinerary` class and the `DefaultBookingServiceFacade.listAllCargos` to understand the flow better."}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4136,"cache_read_input_tokens":57873,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":4136,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":400},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"83d9035c-c20b-4877-bffd-f348c2f149e2","uuid":"7ebce5b4-1758-45d0-9507-b6388e0b968d"}
