{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016R8WvmNorARcTj9zhh9EVU","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<server description=\"Cargo Tracker Jakarta EE Server\">\n     2→\n     3→    <featureManager>\n     4→        <feature>jakartaee-10.0</feature>\n     5→        <feature>localConnector-1.0</feature>\n     6→    </featureManager>\n     7→\n     8→    <httpEndpoint id=\"defaultHttpEndpoint\"\n     9→                  httpPort=\"8080\"\n    10→                  httpsPort=\"9443\"\n    11→                  host=\"*\" />\n    12→\n    13→    <!-- H2 Database -->\n    14→    <library id=\"h2Lib\">\n    15→        <fileset dir=\"${server.config.dir}/lib\" includes=\"h2*.jar\"/>\n    16→    </library>\n    17→\n    18→    <dataSource id=\"CargoTrackerDatabase\" jndiName=\"jdbc/CargoTrackerDatabase\">\n    19→        <jdbcDriver libraryRef=\"h2Lib\"/>\n    20→        <properties.generic\n    21→            URL=\"jdbc:h2:file:./cargo-tracker-data/cargo-tracker-database\"\n    22→            user=\"sa\"\n    23→            password=\"\"/>\n    24→    </dataSource>\n    25→\n    26→    <!-- JMS Configuration using Liberty built-in messaging -->\n    27→    <wasJmsEndpoint id=\"InboundJmsEndpoint\" wasJmsPort=\"7276\" />\n    28→\n    29→    <jmsQueue id=\"CargoHandledQueue\" jndiName=\"jms/CargoHandledQueue\">\n    30→        <properties.wasJms queueName=\"CargoHandledQueue\"/>\n    31→    </jmsQueue>\n    32→    <jmsQueue id=\"MisdirectedCargoQueue\" jndiName=\"jms/MisdirectedCargoQueue\">\n    33→        <properties.wasJms queueName=\"MisdirectedCargoQueue\"/>\n    34→    </jmsQueue>\n    35→    <jmsQueue id=\"DeliveredCargoQueue\" jndiName=\"jms/DeliveredCargoQueue\">\n    36→        <properties.wasJms queueName=\"DeliveredCargoQueue\"/>\n    37→    </jmsQueue>\n    38→    <jmsQueue id=\"HandlingEventRegistrationAttemptQueue\" jndiName=\"jms/HandlingEventRegistrationAttemptQueue\">\n    39→        <properties.wasJms queueName=\"HandlingEventRegistrationAttemptQueue\"/>\n    40→    </jmsQueue>\n    41→    <jmsQueue id=\"RejectedRegistrationAttemptsQueue\" jndiName=\"jms/RejectedRegistrationAttemptsQueue\">\n    42→        <properties.wasJms queueName=\"RejectedRegistrationAttemptsQueue\"/>\n    43→    </jmsQueue>\n    44→\n    45→    <jmsConnectionFactory id=\"jms/DefaultConnectionFactory\" jndiName=\"jms/DefaultConnectionFactory\">\n    46→        <properties.wasJms/>\n    47→    </jmsConnectionFactory>\n    48→\n    49→    <jmsActivationSpec id=\"cargo-tracker/CargoHandledConsumer\">\n    50→        <properties.wasJms destinationRef=\"CargoHandledQueue\" destinationType=\"jakarta.jms.Queue\"/>\n    51→    </jmsActivationSpec>\n    52→    <jmsActivationSpec id=\"cargo-tracker/HandlingEventRegistrationAttemptConsumer\">\n    53→        <properties.wasJms destinationRef=\"HandlingEventRegistrationAttemptQueue\" destinationType=\"jakarta.jms.Queue\"/>\n    54→    </jmsActivationSpec>\n    55→    <jmsActivationSpec id=\"cargo-tracker/DeliveredCargoConsumer\">\n    56→        <properties.wasJms destinationRef=\"DeliveredCargoQueue\" destinationType=\"jakarta.jms.Queue\"/>\n    57→    </jmsActivationSpec>\n    58→    <jmsActivationSpec id=\"cargo-tracker/MisdirectedCargoConsumer\">\n    59→        <properties.wasJms destinationRef=\"MisdirectedCargoQueue\" destinationType=\"jakarta.jms.Queue\"/>\n    60→    </jmsActivationSpec>\n    61→    <jmsActivationSpec id=\"cargo-tracker/RejectedRegistrationAttemptsConsumer\">\n    62→        <properties.wasJms destinationRef=\"RejectedRegistrationAttemptsQueue\" destinationType=\"jakarta.jms.Queue\"/>\n    63→    </jmsActivationSpec>\n    64→\n    65→    <!-- Application configuration -->\n    66→    <webApplication id=\"cargo-tracker\" location=\"cargo-tracker.war\" contextRoot=\"/cargo-tracker\">\n    67→        <classloader apiTypeVisibility=\"+third-party\"/>\n    68→    </webApplication>\n    69→\n    70→    <!-- System property for graph traversal URL -->\n    71→    <jndiEntry jndiName=\"app/configuration/GraphTraversalUrl\"\n    72→               value=\"http://localhost:8080/cargo-tracker/rest/graph-traversal/shortest-path\"/>\n    73→</server>\n    74→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"83d9035c-c20b-4877-bffd-f348c2f149e2","uuid":"68ad6218-ef5a-4a32-bc80-180a4a1f54f8"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01UhDhd6ntj7ZW1WoLwreurx","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.file;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.batch.operations.JobOperator;\n     4→import jakarta.batch.runtime.BatchRuntime;\n     5→import jakarta.ejb.Schedule;\n     6→import jakarta.ejb.Singleton;\n     7→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n     8→\n     9→/**\n    10→ * Periodically scans a certain directory for files and attempts to parse handling event\n    11→ * registrations from the contents by calling a batch job.\n    12→ */\n    13→@Singleton\n    14→@Transactional\n    15→public class UploadDirectoryScanner {\n    16→\n    17→  @Schedule(minute = \"*/2\", hour = \"*\", persistent = false)\n    18→  public void processFiles() {\n    19→    JobOperator jobOperator = BatchRuntime.getJobOperator();\n    20→    jobOperator.start(\"EventFilesProcessorJob\", null);\n    21→  }\n    22→}\n    23→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"83d9035c-c20b-4877-bffd-f348c2f149e2","uuid":"8416048e-bc2b-42ff-b0f8-7718494c3f58"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01MpGZaoWggjt3iKB3bzM8z3","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Two fixes needed:\n\n1. **Remove `@Transactional` from EJB `UploadDirectoryScanner`** - EJBs are transactional by default in Jakarta EE, so `@Transactional` is redundant and Liberty rejects it.\n\n2. **Fix H2 datasource URL** - The `properties.generic` URL attribute isn't being picked up. For H2 with Open Liberty, I need to use a different approach - use `properties` element with the `URL` attribute, or use an in-memory DB to simplify.\n\nLet me also check the persistence.xml to understand how JPA connects to the DB:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2486,"cache_read_input_tokens":98939,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2486,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":264},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"83d9035c-c20b-4877-bffd-f348c2f149e2","uuid":"713045ca-8695-4183-9088-d967e7e4aadc"}
