{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01JAtzmNuyqLMN5FkesCafP8","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I've found and read the contents of all three files you requested. They are located in the `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__jakarta/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/pathfinder/api/` directory.\n\nBrief overview:\n1. GraphTraversalService.java: A REST endpoint service for finding shortest paths between locations. It uses random generation of transit paths and has a `/shortest-path` endpoint.\n2. TransitEdge.java: A model class representing an edge in a transit path, containing voyage number, locations, and dates.\n3. TransitPath.java: A model class representing a complete transit path, which is a list of TransitEdge objects.\n\nWould you like me to provide any additional analysis or explanation about these files?"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"83d9035c-c20b-4877-bffd-f348c2f149e2","uuid":"70eee840-d677-46ea-99c8-9cfd6b3b8509"}
