{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01HtpGCCJFUKeRYVBdEF6AkB","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.util;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.ws.rs.ApplicationPath;\n     4→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Application;\n     5→\n     6→/** Jakarta REST configuration. */\n     7→@ApplicationPath(\"rest\")\n     8→public class RestConfiguration extends Application {\n     9→}\n    10→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"83d9035c-c20b-4877-bffd-f348c2f149e2","uuid":"8f96ef80-1c34-4332-b864-400ff5c00adc"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01XCSebwtRV9FfnTjaPDFxjT","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The simplest fix is to add a JSON-B configuration that handles `LocalDateTime` properly. Since Open Liberty uses JSON-B by default, I can configure it with a `ContextResolver`. But an even simpler approach: add `@JsonbDateFormat` annotations, or better yet, just convert dates to strings in the `TransitEdge`.\n\nActually, the cleanest fix is to register a `ContextResolver<Jsonb>` that configures JSON-B to handle `LocalDateTime`:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":373,"cache_read_input_tokens":135467,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":373,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":460},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"83d9035c-c20b-4877-bffd-f348c2f149e2","uuid":"d47a1967-c02f-4d1e-8e34-95a731d6ad6d"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01XCSebwtRV9FfnTjaPDFxjT","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01SogeAmEvKjZL6oUevmXuHo","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__jakarta/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/util/JsonbContextResolver.java","content":"package org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.util;\n\nimport jakarta.json.bind.Jsonb;\nimport jakarta.json.bind.JsonbBuilder;\nimport jakarta.json.bind.JsonbConfig;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.ext.ContextResolver;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.ext.Provider;\n\n/**\n * JSON-B context resolver that configures proper date/time handling\n * for JAX-RS endpoints.\n */\n@Provider\npublic class JsonbContextResolver implements ContextResolver<Jsonb> {\n\n    @Override\n    public Jsonb getContext(Class<?> type) {\n        JsonbConfig config = new JsonbConfig()\n            .withDateFormat(\"yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ss\", null)\n            .withNullValues(false);\n        return JsonbBuilder.create(config);\n    }\n}\n"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":373,"cache_read_input_tokens":135467,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":373,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":460},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"83d9035c-c20b-4877-bffd-f348c2f149e2","uuid":"2b662525-9f3c-4d05-863c-a8d083957334"}
