{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01XGKeCSwpXR7eHXpJx25Zde","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.util;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.json.bind.Jsonb;\n     4→import jakarta.json.bind.JsonbBuilder;\n     5→import jakarta.json.bind.JsonbConfig;\n     6→import jakarta.ws.rs.ext.ContextResolver;\n     7→import jakarta.ws.rs.ext.Provider;\n     8→\n     9→/**\n    10→ * JSON-B context resolver that configures proper date/time handling\n    11→ * for JAX-RS endpoints.\n    12→ */\n    13→@Provider\n    14→public class JsonbContextResolver implements ContextResolver<Jsonb> {\n    15→\n    16→    @Override\n    17→    public Jsonb getContext(Class<?> type) {\n    18→        JsonbConfig config = new JsonbConfig()\n    19→            .withDateFormat(\"yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ss\", null)\n    20→            .withNullValues(false);\n    21→        return JsonbBuilder.create(config);\n    22→    }\n    23→}\n    24→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"83d9035c-c20b-4877-bffd-f348c2f149e2","uuid":"6b417614-91ae-4036-8ed0-3e56c69d27d6"}
